# Lock files
# Note: package-lock.json is committed for reproducible CI builds

# OpenAPI spec emitted by spora-core's bin/spora-build during the
# api-spec CI job. Never committed — it's a build artifact that
# gen:api consumes on the next step.
docs/.vuepress/openapi.json

# Per-resource API reference pages are generated by scripts/gen-api.mjs
# from docs/.vuepress/openapi.json. They live next to the committed
# api.md shell so VuePress can pick them up at build time, but they
# are NEVER committed — same reasoning as not committing vendor/.
# `prebuild` / `predev` npm hooks run gen:api before VuePress starts,
# so the pages always exist locally and in CI.
docs/reference/api/
